  <p>
    The Independent School of Jakarta will open a purpose-built senior campus in Pondok Indah, South Jakarta, in 2028. The new campus sits 300 metres from the existing junior campus, creating a complete British international school offering the English National Curriculum from age 2 through to A-Levels.
  </p>

  <figure>
    <img src="/images/senior-campus/street-perspective.jpg" alt="Architectural render of the ISJ Senior Campus from street level" class="img-wide" loading="lazy" />
    <figcaption>Architectural sketch of the senior campus in Pondok Indah, South Jakarta.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <h2>A Campus Built Around Learning</h2>

  <p>
    The senior campus will house science laboratories, technology labs, dedicated art and music studios, a theatre, a secondary library, and a football pitch. Every space has been designed to support the breadth of the English National Curriculum at GCSE and A-Level, from the sciences and technology through to the creative and performing arts.
  </p>

  <h2>A Complete Pathway</h2>

  <p>
    Current Year 7 pupils at the junior campus will be the first cohort to progress through to A-Levels at ISJ. For the first time, ISJ families will have a continuous educational journey from Early Years through to university entrance.
  </p>

  <figure>
    <img src="/images/senior-campus/courtyard-colour.jpg" alt="Courtyard view of the ISJ Senior Campus" class="img-wide" loading="lazy" />
    <figcaption>The senior campus courtyard, with the sports hall and classroom blocks.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <h2>The Schools Trust</h2>

  <p>
    ISJ is part of The Schools Trust, which has established 16 British international schools across 11 countries since 2004. Trust schools are ranked 1st and 2nd for A-Level and GCSE results across more than 200 British schools internationally, with 94% of students outperforming the UK national average. Graduates have gone on to Cambridge, Oxford, Imperial, UCL, Edinburgh, the University of Melbourne, Harvard, Georgetown, and the University of Toronto, among others.
  </p>

  <blockquote>
    <p>"Our Year 7s have been with us since they were five. It will be a wonderful feeling to see them grow and graduate with A-Levels."</p>
    <footer>Eileen Fisher, Head of ISJ</footer>
  </blockquote>

  <blockquote>
    <p>"After a couple of detours, I'm really proud of what the ISJ community has built. A new campus and a complete pathway through to A-Levels."</p>
    <footer>Darren Brown, Trustee, The Schools Trust</footer>
  </blockquote>

  <p>
    More details and architectural sketches are available on the <a href="/senior-campus">Senior Campus</a> page.
  </p>

